        "title": "fix(ollama): yield during dense stream processing",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- rebase the Ollama dense stream cooperative-yield fix onto a current maintainer branch, preserving @udaymanish6 as commit author\n- yield and check aborts while draining dense native Ollama NDJSON chunks so one large read cannot monopolize the Gateway event loop\n- preserve caller cancellation semantics during dense stream processing and add regression coverage for timer progress plus abort classification\n\nRefs https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/issues/86599.\nSupersedes https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/pull/86633 as the rebased maintainer branch.\n\n## Verification\n\n- `git diff --check origin/main...HEAD` - passed on final head `e00fa780a23`.\n- `node_modules/.bin/oxfmt --check --threads=1 extensions/ollama/src/stream.ts extensions/ollama/src/stream.test.ts` - passed on final head `e00fa780a23`.\n- `node scripts/run-oxlint.mjs extensions/ollama/src/stream.ts extensions/ollama/src/stream.test.ts` - passed on final head `e00fa780a23`.\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs extensions/ollama/src/stream.test.ts --reporter=dot` - 1 file / 12 tests passed on final head `e00fa780a23`.\n- `.agents/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode branch --base origin/main` - clean after the timer-phase scheduler fix; no accepted/actionable findings; `overall: patch is correct (0.86)`.\n- AWS Crabbox changed gate after the timer-phase scheduler fix: `node scripts/crabbox-wrapper.mjs run --provider aws --target linux --idle-timeout 90m --ttl 180m --timing-json --shell -- \"pnpm check:changed\"`; provider `aws`, lease `cbx_c4c8ac13ee86`, slug `swift-shrimp`, run `run_8fd2ad9a4885`, machine `c7a.8xlarge`, exit `0`, `leaseStopped=true`, lanes `extensions`, `extensionTests`.\n- Final rebase over `ef9e9bf6b92` was clean; the focused final-head diff/format/lint/test proof above was rerun after that rebase.\n- Local Ollama live check was not available in this environment: `ollama` CLI unavailable and `http://127.0.0.1:11434/api/tags` not reachable.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior addressed: dense native Ollama stream chunks now cooperatively yield during parsing instead of draining an entire large read in one synchronous loop, while caller aborts during the drain surface as `aborted` rather than provider `error`.\nReal environment tested: focused local Vitest wrapper in a linked worktree, formatting/lint checks, branch autoreview, and AWS Crabbox Linux changed gate.\nExact steps or command run after this patch: See the Verification section above.\nEvidence after fix: refreshed head `e00fa780a23`; focused stream tests passed with the dense-yield and abort regressions; AWS Crabbox `pnpm check:changed` passed the extension and extension test lanes after the timer-phase scheduler fix.\nObserved result after fix: dense stream unit coverage confirms timer progress during parser drain, aborts scheduled before the first cooperative yield are observed before the stream can finish, aborts during dense processing keep `reason` and assistant `stopReason` set to `aborted`, and changed extension type/lint/import-cycle guards passed remotely.\nWhat was not tested: true live Ollama runtime was not available in this local environment; Windows local-daemon reproduction from https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/issues/86599 was not rerun in this PR. This is one mitigation in the broader event-loop starvation cluster, not the final issue closeout by itself.\n",
